    "LRS) models.",
    "The DR2new dataset exhibits a shallower slope for the PSD of the common red signal than DR2full.",
    "While cosmic strings were a good fit to the common red signal of 6 pulsars of DR2full (Leclere et al. 2023), this is no longer true for DR2new.",
    "This is because the predicted SGWB PSD is generally steeper than the measured correlated red signal in the data, as can be seen in Fig. 16.",
    "For case (ii), we obtain very similar results to those discussed in Leclere et al. (2023)."
